HEADWORD: monetization
<hw>mon`e*ti*za"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or
process of converting into money, or of establishing something (e.g.
gold or silver) as the legal tender of a country; <as>as, the
<ex>monetization</ex> of silver</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monetize</ent>⟦br⟧
